    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lardons are crisp, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>in 80ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[90ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[60ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong>, your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and your<strong> wholegrain mustard </strong>– this is your<strong> stock</strong></p><p>Once the leek has softened, add <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and cook for a further 1-2 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
