    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>stock</strong> to the pan with your <strong>Chinese rice wine </strong>and a generous crack of<strong> pepper</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 3-4 min or until slightly thickened</p><p>Once the chicken is cooked, transfer it to a clean board and shred it apart using two forks – this technique is known as 'pulling'</p><p>Reserve the tray with the baking paper and add the <strong>chopped waxy potatoes</strong>,<strong> </strong>a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
