    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim, then add your <strong>green beans </strong>to a large piece of <strong>tin foil </strong>(or two!) with the <strong>remaining chopped garlic</strong>, a large knob of<strong> butter </strong>and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Scrunch the edges of the foil around the green beans to form a sealed parcel[s] and add to a separate baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until tender with a slight bite – these are your <strong>garlicky green beans</strong></p>",
